DECEMBER 31, 2006 WERE $5.76 BILLION AND $5.98 BILLION. THE FAIR VALUE OF THE COMPANY'S DEBT IS DETERMINED ON A PRESENT VALUE BASIS USING THE MOST RECENT OBSERVED MARKET YIELD.

THE

FAIR VALUE OF COMMERCIAL PAPER INCLUDED IN DEBT OUTSTANDING AT DECEMBER 31, 2007 AND 2006 APPROXIMATED ITS BOOK VALUE BECAUSE OF ITS SHORT-TERM NATURE. FOR OTHER

DEBT, THE FAIR VALUE ESTIMATE WAS BASED UPON THE BID PRICE AT DECEMBER 31, 2007 AND 2006.

